1. In that the preaching Elders of greater Presbytery, were ordained to their office by a queſtionable power (by the Biſhops) which they have not to this day renounced. 2. In that the ruling Elders are made by a power as queſtionable, (though not ſo Antichriſtia
                     •
                  ) to wit, an Ordinance of Parl. as M. Saltmarſh hath lately obſerved, in his Reaſons diſcuſſing the divine right of Presbytery, p. 3, 4. And ſo much for the teſtimony of the learned.
